UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Innovation, Partnerships And Engagement: Public And Private, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. description.narrative: In 2021, UNICEF continued to work with governmental and civil society partners to implement the Education COVID-19 emergency response plan and protocols, which allowed children to continue learning in safe schools. In collaboration with the National Institute for the Development of Education (INDE), World Bank (WB), Calouste Gulbenkian Foundation (FCG), and Minho University, UNICEF successfully contributed to the reform of the curriculum resulting in the availability of complete sets of textbooks and resources for students and teachers for grades 1 and 3. These have started; ;being piloted during the 2021/2022 school year. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/01/2022
